generally this is OK, but there are cases when this would behave differently if you remove the catch/throw. Consider the following
try{...}
catch(ChildException e){throw e;}
catch(ParentException e){//do something}

this block of code would behave differently if you remove the catch/throw of ChildException.

So please make sure there is no such exception hierarchy in the code you touched.

